{"type":"text","timestamp":1775839097487,"sessionID":"ses_287c1a8faffeeokE1uwfD9WZT1","part":{"id":"prt_d7841e8e9001eJPv8g2ZSroJrF","messageID":"msg_d7841a3270014zEmR1P3LIpaZ8","sessionID":"ses_287c1a8faffeeokE1uwfD9WZT1","type":"text","text":"Done! I've created `proposal.md` for the agentcube project at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md`.\n\nThe proposal includes all the requested sections:\n\n1. **Purpose** — Defines the `AgentRuntime` CRD types to enable Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration for AI agent workloads\n\n2. **Scope** — \n   - In scope: Package structure, API group (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`), types defined, scheme registration, kubebuilder markers, code generation, and generated client surface\n   - Out of scope: CodeInterpreter CRD, Workload Manager HTTP API, reconciler logic, Helm chart rendering, RBAC\n\n3. **Design** — File layout, type definitions (AgentRuntime, AgentRuntimeSpec, AgentRuntimeStatus, shared types), scheme registration, and code generation pipeline\n\n4. **Impact analysis** — Files created, files generated, downstream consumers (client-go, Workload Manager, Helm charts), and breaking change risk assessment\n\n5. **Alternatives considered** — Four alternatives analyzed:\n   - Standalone CRD YAML (no Go types) — rejected\n   - Kubebuilder/controller-runtime scaffolding — rejected  \n   - Multi-version API from day one — rejected\n   - Embed full `corev1.PodTemplateSpec` — rejected\n\n6. **Dependencies** and **Verification** sections are also included","time":{"start":1775839097484,"end":1775839097484}}}
